body:
Fixes one part of https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4228

I also added tests for the equivalent list and tuple operations, but they seemed to work as is.

comment_data.body:
```suggestion
        elif dst_type.is_cpp_class and dst_type.can_coerce_from_pyobject(env):
```

(make it a little more specific)

                         if isinstance(value, CoerceToPyTypeNode):

+        elif dst_type.can_coerce_from_pyobject(env):

comment_data.body:
Shouldn't we just call `ExprNode.coerce_to()` as a general fallback?
(BTW, `can_coerce_from_pyobject()` was just added later than `create_from_py_utility_code()` to avoid always doing the actual work, if all we need is know if it can be done.)

                         if isinstance(value, CoerceToPyTypeNode):
                             value = value.arg
                         item.value = value.coerce_to(member.type, env)
+        elif dst_type.is_cpp_class and dst_type.can_coerce_from_pyobject(env):
+            # not guaranteed that we can coerce from this particular PyObject, but worth a try
+            # Note that other places seem to try calling create_from_py_utility_code instead
+            return CoerceFromPyTypeNode(dst_type, self, env)

comment_data.body: I think we can still keep the loops, even if they don't raise errors any more. This is quite clearly the only place where such code was exercised. Not all examples in error tests must fail with an error. Some are just there to say "see, the rest is wrong, but this similar code is accepted". We should get notified when that behaviour ever changes, especially by accident.

milestone.description:
Goals:
 New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
 Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3`.
 Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
 Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).
